A MAN has been arrested and &pound;700,000 of drugs seized during a police raid.
Officers searched a flat in St Mungo Place, Glasgow, at about 7.15pm yesterday and made the discovery.
Heroin with a street value of &pound;665,000 and cocaine worth about &pound;35,000 was found in the property.
A 48-year-old man has been arrested in connection with the haul.
A report is to be sent to the procurator fiscal and the man is due to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court tomorrow.
 
